ely%20secured%20to%20prevent%20them%20from%20flying%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20Store%20your%20items%20securely%20in%20overhead%20compartments%20to%20avoid%20spills%20or%20falls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E6.%C2%A0Be%20calm.%20Turbulence%20is%20normal%3B%20stay%20relaxed%20and%20avoid%20panicking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E7.%C2%A0If%20you%C2%A0have%20to%C2%A0use%20the%20restroom%2C%20wait%20for%20a%20calm%20moment%20before%20getting%20up%2C%20and%20use%20handrails%20for%20stability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAir%20turbulence%3A%20Causes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETurbulence%20can%C2%A0be%20caused%C2%A0by%20atmospheric%20conditions%20such%20as%20thunderstorms%2C%20jet%20streams%2C%20or%20changes%20in%20air%20pressure.%20Experts%20believe%20air%20turbulence%20is%20becoming%20more%20frequent%C2%A0due%20to%20changes%20in%20climate%20patterns%20caused%20by%C2%A0climate%20change.%20While%20severe%20turbulence%C2%A0events%20remain%C2%A0rare%2C%20pilots%C2%A0are%20trained%C2%A0to%20handle%20them%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECaptain%20Chris%20Hammond%2C%20a%20retired%20pilot%20with%2043%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20explained%C2%A0to%20the%20BBC%C2%A0how%20they%20respond%20to%20such%20a%20situation.%C2%A0Their%20first%20step%20is%20to%20make%20or%20think%20of%20an%20announcement%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cthat%C2%A0won't%C2%A0upset%20the%20passengers%20too%20much.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20explained%2C%C2%A0%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20see%20it%20coming%2C%20you%20can%20take%20it%20leisurely%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0before%20adding%20that%20they%20keep%20their%20fingers%20crossed%20in%20case%20of%20clear%20air%20turbulence.%20(Clear%20air%20turbulence%20occurs%20in%20cloudless%20skies%20and%20cannot%C2%A0be%20seen).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716449700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Flc139794_singapore-airlines_625x300_23_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fflight-turbulence