%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fuk-polls-43-say-labour-leader-starmer-better-pm-than-sunak-pre-poll-survey-suggests%2Famp_articleshow%2F110349445.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fuk-polls-43-say-labour-leader-starmer-better-pm-than-sunak-pre-poll-survey-suggests%2Famp_articleshow%2F110349445.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rishi%20Sunak%20Blindsided%20His%20Own%20Finance%20Minister%20With%20Sudden%20UK%20Poll%20Call%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EUK%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20decision%20to%20stake%20the%20Conservative%20Party's%20future%20on%20a%20rare%20summer%20election%20was%20so%20secret%20that%20even%20his%20chancellor%20of%20the%20exchequer%2C%20Jeremy%20Hunt%2C%20appeared%20surprised%20by%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHunt's%20allies%20were%20unaware%20enough%20of%20the%20snap%20election%20called%20by%20Sunak%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20some%20feared%20a%20rumored%20big%20announcement%20meant%20that%20the%20chancellor%20was%20about%20to%20be%20replaced%20in%20a%20reshuffle%2C%20according%20to%20people%20familiar%20with%20thinking%20in%20the%20Treasury.%20As%20the%20prime%20minister%20prepared%20to%20reveal%20his%20decision%20in%20a%20news%20conference%20outside%2010%20Downing%20St.%2C%20Hunt%20was%20busy%20canceling%20media%20appearances%20to%20speak%20about%20the%20morning's%20inflation%20data%20and%20shortening%20a%20trip%20to%20a%20meeting%20of%20Group%20of%20Seven%20finance%20ministers%20on%20Thursday%20in%20Italy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20ministers%20backed%20the%20election%20decision%2C%20with%20Communities%20Secretary%20Michael%20Gove%20praising%20the%20move%20in%20Cabinet%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20discussions.%20But%20disappointment%20was%20a%20common%20sentiment%20among%20Tory%20MPs%2C%20including%20some%20ministers%2C%20as%20they%20absorbed%20the%20implications%20of%20a%20vote%20that%20could%20cost%20scores%20of%20them%20seats%2C%20with%20Hunt%20seen%20as%20among%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20Cabinet%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20had%20long%20ago%20accepted%20Sunak's%20calls%20to%20%26quot%3Bstick%20to%20the%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20they%20interpreted%20as%20waiting%20for%20the%20economic%20backdrop%20to%20improve%20as%20forecast%20later%20in%20the%20year.%20That%20was%20reliant%20on%20a%20series%20of%20economic%20events%20to%20show%20Britain%20had%20turned%20the%20corner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHunt%20had%20as%20recently%20as%20last%20week%20suggested%20he%20might%20again%20reduce%20payroll%20taxes%20in%20an%20autumn%20fiscal%20statement%2C%20something%20that%20will%20now%20be%20left%20to%20the%20next%20government.%20Foreign%20Secretary%20David%20Cameron%2C%20a%20former%20prime%20minister%20now%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%2C%20on%20May%2012%20endorsed%20plans%20to%20wait%20until%20later%20in%20the%20year%20for%20an%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20support%20of%20a%20summer%20vote%20raised%20questions%20about%20how%20motivated%20the%20party%20will%20be%20to%20contest%20Labour%20leader%20Keir%20Starmer's%20bid%20to%20become%20prime%20minister.%20One%20sitting%20government%20minister%2C%20speaking%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20said%20the%20July%204%20date%20was%20a%20terrible%20idea%20given%20the%20Conservatives%20have%20been%20polling%2020%20points%20behind%20the%20main%20opposition%20Labour%20Party.%20A%20second%20minister%20said%20the%20timing%20suggested%20Sunak%20had%20given%20up%20and%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20prime%20minister%20any%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20months%2C%20Sunak%20aides%20had%20declined%20to%20say%20when%20exactly%20the%20election%20would%20be%20held%2C%20frustrating%20bankbench%20Tory%20MPs%20who%20complained%20he%20was%20using%20the%20threat%20to%20keep%20them%20from%20joining%20efforts%20to%20replace%20him%20as%20leader.%20Conservative%20rebels%20had%20argued%20that%20the%20party%20was%20facing%20oblivion%20squeezed%20by%20Labour%20and%20the%20Liberal%20Democrats%20on%20the%20left%20and%20the%20Reform%20UK%20party%20founded%20by%20Brexit%20campaigner%20Nigel%20Farage%20on%20the%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20backbench%20Tory%20MPs%20took%20to%20social%20media%20to%20criticize%20the%20election%20timing%2C%20with%20Tracey%20Crouch%20and%20Dehenna%20Davison%20writing%20on%20X%20that%20they%20were%20disappointed%20that%20they%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20do%20things%20they'd%20been%20hoping%20to%20achieve%20in%20Parliament.%20Indeed%2C%20the%20sudden%20election%20likely%20means%20some%20key%20pieces%20of%20legislation%20he%20promised%20in%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20Conference%20and%20King's%20Speech%20last%20year%20will%20be%20left%20undone%2C%20including%20a%20progressive%20ban%20on%20smoking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Sunak%20appears%20to%20have%20calculated%20that%20there%20was%20more%20advantage%20in%20a%20vote%20that%20may%20coincide%20with%20flights%20deporting%20asylum%20seekers%20to%20Rwanda%2C%20an%20issue%20he%20wants%20to%20be%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20campaign.%20Sunak%20has%20indicated%20that%20he%20hopes%20the%20first%20flights%20would%20leave%20by%20early%20July%2C%20giving%20him%20a%20talking%20point%20to%20counter%20a%20key%20driver%20of%20votes%20to%20Reform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnger%20within%20Tory%20ranks%20wasn't%20just%20directed%20at%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20election%3A%20it%20was%20also%20leveled%20at%20Sunak's%20mode%20of%20announcement%2C%20delivered%20while%20soaking%20in%20the%20rain%20outside%20Downing%20Street%20and%20almost%20drowned%20out%20by%20music%20from%20a%20protester.%20Several%20Tory%20politicians%2C%20including%20a%20cabinet%20minister%2C%20told%20Bloomberg%20privately%20that%20he%20should%20have%20had%20an%20umbrella%20or%20given%20his%20statement%20inside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20a%20room%20of%20100%20or%20so%20Conservative%20members%20of%20Parliament%20an