%20phenomenon%2C%20which%20researchers%20say%20comes%20amid%20unusually%20rapid%20warming%20in%20the%20region%2C%20was%20first%20observed%20in%20the%20northwestern%20state%20in%202018%2C%20scientists%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-rivers-orange-permafrost-melting-iron-acidic-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20Jenny%20McGrath%20in%20January.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20have%20been%20stumped%20by%20it%20for%20years.%20But%20their%20findings%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3De4eebf627b72abfc763e3ff1a92ddbee7dd89a18c94317ab0eae4b90a98b5a6d%26postID%3D664ea753f69613c040c727fa%26postSlug%3D75-alaskan-rivers-turning-orange-even-seen-from-space-study-2024-5%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs43247-024-01446-z%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20Monday%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20Communications%20Earth%20%26amp%3B%20Environment%20journal%2C%20say%20that%20the%20waterways'%20rusty%20color%20likely%20comes%20from%20minerals%20uncovered%20by%20the%20thaw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreviously%20locked%20beneath%20Alaska's%20permafrost%2C%20these%20minerals%20are%20now%20exposed%20to%20water%20and%20oxygen%2C%20causing%20them%20to%20release%20acid%20and%20metals%20like%20zinc%2C%20copper%2C%20iron%2C%20and%20aluminum%2C%20the%20study%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dissolved%20iron%20is%20thought%20to%20be%20the%20main%20culprit%20behind%20the%20%26quot%3Brusting%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20rivers%2C%20which%20typically%20occurs%20in%20July%20and%20August%20when%20the%20thaw%20is%20the%20most%20pronounced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20implications%20of%20the%20melt%20go%20far%20beyond%20color.%20These%20waters%20are%20becoming%20so%20acidic%20that%20some%20are%20registering%20pH%20levels%20of%202.6%2C%20or%20between%20the%20equivalent%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usgs.gov%2Fmedia%2Fimages%2Fph-scale%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacidity%20of%20lemon%20juice%20and%20orange%20juice.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPure%20water%20has%20a%20pH%20value%20of%207.%20Rivers%20and%20lakes%20typically%20have%20a%20pH%20value%20of%206.5%20to%208%2C%20and%20acid%20rain%20has%20a%20pH%20value%20of%204.2%20to%204.4.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222460%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20image%20of%20the%20clear%20Akillik%20River%20in%202016%20and%20the%20orange%20river%20in%202018%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a1649043bb77284b9ca2cd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20stream%20tributary%20of%20the%20Akillik%20River%20in%20Kobuk%20Valley%20National%20Park%2C%20Alaska%20turned%20orange%20between%202016%20(left)%20and%202018%20(right).%3Cp%3EJon%20O'Donnell%2FNational%20Park%20Service%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20findings%20have%20considerable%20implications%20for%20drinking%20water%20supplies%20and%20subsistence%20fisheries%20in%20rural%20Alaska%2C%26quot%3B%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20added%20that%20the%20region%20has%20already%20suffered%20the%20%26quot%3Bcomplete%20loss%26quot%3B%20of%20two%20fish%20species%20due%20to%20the%20acidity%3A%20juvenile%20Dolly%20Varden%20trout%20and%20the%20Slimy%20Sculpin.%20Chum%20salmon%20and%20whitefish%20are%20also%20at%20risk%20of%20population%20decline%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20changes%20could%20be%20devastating%20for%20indigenous%20tribes%20in%20the%20region%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uaf.edu%2Ftribal%2Facademics%2F112%2Funit-3%2Ftribalhuntingandfishingrightssubsistenceanilca1980.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erely%20heavily%20on%20fishing%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20researchers%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2075%20orange%20streams%20observed%20were%20scattered%20across%20northern%20Alaska%20over%20a%20span%20of%20about%20600%20miles%2C%20the%20study%20said.%20All%20of%20them%20were%20in%20remote%20areas%2C%20miles%20away%20from%20human%20activity%20that%20could%20impact%20land%2C%20such%20as%20roads%20or%20mining.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20highlighted%20satellite%20images%20of%20the%20Agashashok%20River%2C%20a%20tributary%20of%20the%20Kuguroruk%20River%2C%20and%20the%20Anaktok%20Creek%20tributary%20of%20the%20Salmon%20River%20in%20northwest%20Alaska.%20They%20said%20all%20three%20have%20turned%20considerably%20redder%20in%20the%20summer%20months%20of%20the%20last%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223625%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20orange%20tributary%20joins%20the%20Kugaroruk%20River%20in%20Alaska.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664ebd7320abc1efe8fcc286%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222718%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20orange%20tributary%20joins%20the%20Kuguroruk%20River%20in%20Alaska.%3Cp%3EJoshua%20Koch%2C%20US%20Geological%20Survey%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20warn%20that%20Alaska%20is%20warming%20at%20a%20rate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.ametsoc.org%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Fclim%2F36%2F13%2FJCLI-D-22-0434.1.xml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20to%20three%20times%20the%20global%20average.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnca2023.globalchange.gov%2Fchapter%2F29%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprojected%20in%20November%20that%20the%20state%20would%20need%20an%20estimated%20%244.8%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20infrastructure%20repair%20and%20adaptation%20over%20the%20next%2050%20years%20due%20to%20rising%20temperatures%20and%20damage%20from%20flooding%2C%20erosion%2C%20and%20permafrost%20thaw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20administration's%20multiagency%20report%2C%20Alaska's%20fishing%20and%20tourism%20industries%2C%20which%20collectively%20provide%20more%20than%2090%2C000%20jobs%20and%20%242.57%20billion%20in%2